JOHANNESBURG – A consignment of drugs worth R4.5-million was seized at OR Tambo International Airport in Johannesburg, the South African Revenue Services (Sars) said on Wednesday. Sars spokesperson Sandile Memela said a passenger from Lagos, Nigeria, carrying 15.1kg of crystal/ephedrine was intercepted by Sars Customs officials upon arriving from Ethiopia on Tuesday. READ: Dubai-bound man caught with over R10m at Cape Town airport “The passenger was intercepted with two pieces of check-in luggage that were searched to reveal a whitish rough substance that was concealed at the bottom,” Memela said in a statement. “A drug test for crystal/ephedrine meth was conducted which tested positive and the passenger was handed over to the South African Police Service for further investigation.” READ: Customs officials seize cocaine worth R600,000 on plane at OR Tambo Memela said the successful operation was a result of a joint collaboration between Sars, police and officials from the Airports Company of South Africa (ACSA). African News Agency